
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/vendor/rainbow/themes/github.css" />
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/app/index.built.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/app.css" />
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="header">
      <div class="container blurb">
        <div class="row navbar">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <img id="logo" src="/img/mojo-js-transparent.png"></img>

            <div class="navlinks">
              <a href="/docs">Documentation</a>
              <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
              <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/mojojs">Community</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row caption">
          <div class="col-md-3"></div>
          <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
            <h2>A plugin-based framework for creating powerful web applications</h2>

            <p>
              Mojo.js is a modular, isomorphic web framework that allows you cherry-pick exactly what features you want to use for your application. 
            </p>

            <div class="download-buttons">
              <a class="btn download-button" href="#">Download</a>
              <a class="btn download-button get-started" href="#">Get Started</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-3"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="row caption">
          
          <div class="col-md-12">
            {{
              idePrep: {
                projectName: "Chatroom Example",
                sourceDir: __dirname + "/_examples/chatroom"
              }
            }}
          </div>


        </div>

      </div>
      <div class="subheader">
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container content">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-heart-empty"></span>&nbsp;Simple</h3>
          <p> 
            Love Backbone.js? You'll appreciate Mojo's straight-forward, coherent API. 
            <!-- explicity -->
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-link"></span>&nbsp;Compatible</h3>
          <p> 
            Mojo easily works with just about any library. Work with jQuery, Angular, React, Backbone, 
    whatever you want. Check out the available <a href="#">cross-framework plugins</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    
       <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-wrench"></span>&nbsp;Modular</h3>
          <p>
            Mojo is composed of many loosely coupled, and highly extendable libraries. Pick whatever you want to suite your application needs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flash"></span>&nbsp;Fast</h3>
          <p>
            Mojo works very well with old browsers (IE 7+), along with newer browsers. <a href="/perf">Check out the benchmarks</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-random"></span>&nbsp;Isomorphic</h3>
          <p>
            Easily write JavaScript apps that run on the server, and the browser. Check out <a href="https://github.com/mojo-js/mojojs.com">this website</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h3><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok"></span>&nbsp;Testable</h3>
          <p>
            Writing unit tests is a breeze. You can even run them in Node.js! Check out <a href="#">writing unit tests with Mojo</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content-footer">
    </div>

  </body>

  <script type="text/javascript" src="/vendor/js/rainbow-custom.min.js"></script>
</html>
